description:
&lt;p&gt;NWSSP Legal &amp; Risk Services Clinical Negligence team requires a talented and committed Senior Solicitor. The division manages clinical negligence claims on behalf of Local Health Boards and NHS Trusts in Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is varied and includes assisting the team manager with the day to day operation of a busy clinical negligence claim caseload including litigated and pre-ligated files, arising out of the Hywel Dda LHB and Powys TLHB. The role will also require the candidate to manage inquest files and to provide general healthcare advice to clients. The successful candidate will have access to supervision when required but will generally work autonomously and will provide supervision to more junior members of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior member of the team, the candidate will also be expected to train, mentor and professionally supervise more junior members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate for the above position must have good communication skills, a confident approach to work and can demonstrate our core values:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Listening and Learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working Together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking Responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovating&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 18/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Anne Sparkes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Anne.Sparkes@wales.nhs.uk &lt;/p&gt;
